  if feature != 'av_total':
    # Set the figure size
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 3))
    # Create the histogram using seaborn
    sns.scatterplot(boston,x=feature, y='av_total')
    sns.regplot(boston, x=feature, y='av_total', scatter_kws={'s': 50, 'color': 'pink'}, line_kws={'color': 'red'})

    # Set the title and x-label
    plt.title(f'Scatter Plot of av_total = {feature} ')
    plt.xlabel(feature)
    plt.ylabel('Assessed Value')
    # Display the plot
    plt.show()
